       HOOK_HOME OPTIONS

       hhoommee   Example: /home/uweb/%u

              Scope: global / stanza

              If "home" is enabled on the manage list, this directive supplies
              the template for creating user home directories.

OOPPTTIIOONNSS
       HOOK_SCRIPT OPTIONS

       ssccrriippttaadddd
              Example: /bin/echo %u added

              Scope: global / stanza

              If "script" is enabled on the manage list, this directive speci-
              fies a script/program to run after user record addition.  %u  is
              replaced  with the username, %g with the group name, and %c with
              the user profile name.

       ssccrriippttddeell
              Example: /bin/echo %u deleted

              Scope: global / stanza

              If "script" is enabled on the manage list, this directive speci-
              fies  a  script/program  to run after user record removal. %u is
              replaced with the username, %g with the group name, and %c  with
              the user profile name.

OOPPTTIIOONNSS
       HOOK_WEB OPTIONS

       aappaacchhee Example: false

              Scope: global / stanza

              If "web" is enabled on the "manage" list, this directive toggles
              configuration of apache for this user type.

       aappaacchheessiitteess
              Example: /etc/apache2/sites-enabled/

              Scope: global / stanza

              If "web" is enabled in the manage list and apache=true for  this
              user  type,  use  this  directory to create and remove user web-
              sites.

       aappaacchheeddoommaaiinn
              Example: example.com

              Scope: global / stanza

              If "web" is enabled in the manage list and apache=true for  this
              user type, use this domain for the created VirtualHost.

       aappaacchheeppoorrtt
              Example: 80

              Scope: global / stanza

              If  "web" is enabled in the manage list and apache=true for this
              user type, use this port for webserver logic.

       aappaacchheeccttll
              Example: /etc/init.d/apache2

              Scope: global / stanza

              If "web" is enabled in the manage list and apache=true for  this
              user type, use this script to conpol apache.

